Incident.Summary: DUI#23-092 on Sunday, September 10, 2023 at approximately 1718 hours, I, Senior Trooper Dugue ID# 5832 responding to a three vehicle personal injuries collision on southbound Interstate 95 north of Maryland Route 216 in Laurel, in Howard County, Maryland. Erick Rolando Portillo Ayala DOB; 06/17/1997 was the driver at fault and later was arrested for Driving Under the Influence of Alcohol. 1st offense

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: DUI# 23-092 Interactions/Interviews were captured/recorded on my body camera. MSP Marked Unit A-4 in-car camera was not functioning during that time. Defendant: Erick Rolando Portillo Ayala Date of Birth:06/17/1997 Date of Arrest: 9/10/2023 Times of Arrest: 1835 hours DL: P-634-234-744-452 *******Related reports: ACRS:23-MSP-031828 ********* TRAINING/CERTIFICATES: * Graduated with distinction from the University of Maryland Institute of Advanced Law Enforcement Studies, DUI Institute, Session XIII. I am trained by the Maryland State Police and the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration to administer standardized field sobriety tests. I am a certified Radar and Lidar operator. VEHICLE IN MOTION (PHASE 1) On Sunday, September 10, 2023 at approximately 1718 hours, I was working on uniform patrol, operatingmarked MSP unit, A-4. I was stopped at the crossover of southbound interstate 95 north of Maryland Route 216, monitoring traffic. During that time, I heard a loud boom, and I looked at the right shoulder of southbound 95 north of Maryland Route 216 where a black Jeep Compass with a Virginia registration plate VZT6520 was struck and pushed into a ditch by a white BMW M3, with a Maryland registration plate M3NACER, and sustained severe front and rear-end damage. Then I saw the white BMW come back from the right shoulder on the roadway by crossing lane four, and strike the right side of a red Nissan Altima with a Maryland registration plate MIL2965. After the red Nissan was impacted by the white BMW, the red Nissan was subsequently forced to lane number two and made contact with unidentified tractor trailer. The white BMW continued by crossing lane two, one, the left shoulder of the highway and drove into the ditch into the shrubs. At that point, I immediately activated my emergency equipment and contacted the Waterloo Barrack about the incident through the radio. I went to the right shoulder first and made contact with the black Jeep Compass occupants. The driver and front passenger were trapped inside their vehicle in the ditch against a tree. With the help of a good Samaritan and my rescue tools (bolt cutter) I was able to open the driver side door of the Jeep Compass. The driver of the Jeep Compass was identified as Robert Orville Chapman Jr. (D.O.B: 08/08/1981) and the front passenger was identified as Christina Marie Springhetti (D.O.B: 12/06/1979). Robert Orville Chapman Jr. stated his vehicle was struck by the white BMW while he was stopped on the right shoulder. Robert Orville ChapmanJr. and Christina Marie Springhetti were physically okay. Chapman Jr. provided a written statement, which is attached. At that point I called for assistance from Howard County Fire Rescue/EMS and SHA. I made contact with two witnesses on the scene, Bonnie Dang (D.O.B: 03/01/1995) and Belinda Anderson (D.O.B.: 11/22/1997). Both witnesses stated that the driver of the white BMW M3 was driving erratically by going in and out of traffic lanes and overtaking other vehicles aggressively at a high rate of speed. Please see the attachment for the witness statement from Anderson and Dang. Cpl. Dull was on his way to assist, and I went to the left shoulder of the highway to make contact with the occupants of the white BMW. At approximately 1723 hours, Cpl. Dull ID# 6466 arrived at the scene. Cpl. Dull made contact with the four occupants of the red Nissan Altima and obtained the information of the occupants. The driver of the Nissan Altima was identified as Shania Shadique Daley DOB: 02/06/1999 African American female. The front passenger was identified as Sia Musa, (D.O.B: 03/23/1989). A preschool age child was sitting in the rear left in a child car seat, Sage Sesay (D.O.B: 12/23/2018) and a school-age girl was sitting in the rear right side passengers seat, Saniya Sesay (D.O.B: 06/23/2013). PERSONAL CONTACT (PHASE 2) When I arrived at the left shoulder, I saw the BMW M3 in the ditch against the shrubbery with severe front-end damage and a combination of airbags in the vehicle were deployed. I saw two Hispanic males who were sitting outside. Both males were crying and asked for medical help. I made contact with the first Hispanic male, he was identified by his Maryland license as Erick Rolando Portillo Ayala (D.O.B: 06/17/1997). The second Hispanic male was identified by his Maryland license as Medardo Jose Portillo Ayala (D.O.B: 11/05/2001). Medardo Jose Portillo Ayala was crying and asking for help for his wrist pain. Medardo Jose Portillo Ayala advised he was in pain and needed his mother. Then, I spoke to Erick Rolando Portillo Ayala. I asked him if he was the driver of the white BMW M3. Erick Rolando Portillo Ayala stated that yes, he was the driver of the white BMW M3 and that he messed up and was very sorry about what happened. I asked Erick Rolando Portillo Ayala where he was coming from. Erick Rolando Portillo Ayala stated that he was coming the Baltimore Ravens Football game. I immediately detected a strong odor of an alcoholic beverage emanating from Erick Rolando Portillo Ayalas breath and person. His eyes were glassy and bloodshot. I asked him how many alcoholic beverages he had to drink. Erick Rolando Portillo Ayala stated to have been drinking and he was really sorry. Erick Rolando Portillo Ayala tried to stand but he was unable to stand up on his own. I went to check on the white BMW M3, and thats when I saw in plain view one empty 750ML bottle Dusse cognac, one full bottle of Smirnoff beer, one can of Hefeweizen beer. Shortly after, Howard County EMS personnel arrived at the scene and rendered medical help to Erick Rolando Portillo Ayala and Medardo Jose Portillo Ayala. Soon after that, Erick Rolando Portillo Ayala and Medardo Jose Portillo Ayala were transported to Howard General Hospital for further medical evaluation (Run #23-29627). Due to my observation of and strong indicators of alcohol present, I believed Erick Rolando Portillo Ayala was driving under the influence of alcohol. At approximately 1738 hours, TFC Shiveler ID# 6683 reported to the Waterloo Barrack to pick up a Blood Kit. At approximately 1820 hours, TFC Shiveler reported at the Howard General Hospital to make contact with Erick Rolando Portillo Ayala for the blood draw. Please see TFC Shivelers supplement report for the DR-15 Advice of Rights and the blood draw form MSP-034 and process. At approximately 1900 hours I reported to Howard General Hospital and contacted Erick Rolando Portillo Ayala. I returned the Accident Exchange form and provided further information of the DUI process. PRE-ARREST SCREENING (PHASE 3) PRE-ARREST SCREENING (PHASE 3) N/A HORIZONTAL GAZE NYSTAGMUS N/A WALK AND TURN N/A ONE LEG STAND N/A PRELIMINARYBREATHTEST: N/A Photographs uploaded to Veri Pic. All events occurred in Howard County, Maryland. Case Status: Open, pending on Blood Result.

On 9/10/2023 at approximately 1820 hours, I responded to Howard County General Hospital with a MSP bloodkit, to assist Sr./Tpr. Dugue #5832 with his investigation. I was advised the driver in the collision I was looking for was identified as Erick Rolando Portillo Ayala. As I walked into Portillo Ayalas room, I detected the strong odor of an alcoholic beverage, emanating from inside the room. I spoke with Portillo Ayala, confirmed by his MVA photo. I asked Portillo Ayala if he was driving earlier today, and what vehicle he was driving. Portillo Ayala advised he was in a crash leaving the Ravens game, and he was operating a white BMW. I asked Portillo Ayala if he had consumed any alcohol earlier in the day, and he advised he had 1/3 bottle of 750ml Cognac, and 4 tall Coors Light beers inside the stadium. I advised Portillo Ayala that I was here to offer him the DR-015, Advice of Rights, given the suspected nature of alcohol being a contributing factor in the vehicle collision earlier. I provided Portillo Ayala a copy of the DR-015, and advised him to follow along as I read the form in its entirety. At the conclusion of the form, Portillo Ayala apologized for the collision, and he agreed to submit to the bloodkit test, and signed indicating the same at 1835 hours. The blooddraw was conducted at 1857 hours by Registered Nurse (R.N.) Rebecca Bungard, and I witnessed the blooddraw in its entirety. After the forms were completed and signed, I handed Portillo Ayala his copy of his DR-015, and secured the bloodkit in my vehicle. The bloodkit was transported to the Maryland State Police, Waterloo Barrack, where the bloodkit was processed and sent to Maryland State Police Forensic Science Division, as per policy. Copies of documentation were relayed to Sr./Tpr. Dugue.

On October 24, 2023, I received the result of Blood Test for Alcohol concentration for Erick Portillo Ayala. The Blood specimen was found to contain an alcohol concentration of .17 grams of alcohol per 100 milliliters of blood. Erick Portillo Ayalla will be contacted by telephone and he will be served with the Blood result and appropriate traffic violation charges. Case remains pending. All events occurred in Howard County in Maryland.

On Monday, October 30th, 2023 at approximately 1350 hours, I called Erick Rolando Portillo Ayalaon his cellular phone to request a meeting with him. The phone ring with no answer. 0n 10/31/2023 at approximately 1338 hours, I sent an email to Erick Portillo GMAILs account andadvised him to contact the Waterloo Barrack. Erick Portillo did not reply to the email On 10/3/2023 approximately 1450 hours, I called Erick Portillo on his cellular phone, the phone went straight to his voicemail. On 11/1/2023 at approximately 1550 hours, I contacted the MSP College Park Barrack and spoke with D.O officer Cpl. Aaron Williams. I asked to send a trooper for a residence check for Erick Portillo. I was advised by Cpl. Williams that he will send a trooper to Erick Portillos residence after rush hour. On Thursday, November 2, 2023 at approximately 1900 hours, I received a call from Cpl. Williams. Cpl. Williams advised a residence check was conducted and Erick Portillo was no longer living in that address. On Saturday, November 4, 20223 at approximately 2330 hours, I called Erick Portilllo on his (202) 340-0760 telephone number. Erick Portillo answered the called, and I instructed him to report to the Waterloo Barrack to meet with me. Erick Portillo advised he will be there on Sunday, November 05, 2023 at 11pm. On Sunday, November 05, 2023, at approximately 2315 hours, Erick Portillo reported to the Waterloo Barrack and I met with him. I served Erick Portillo the Blood Test Result, the DR 15 A and Erick Portillo received and signed the documents. Erick Portillo was charged accordingly with multiple traffic violation for the DUI, including a Civil Citation(4Z2235281) for the open alcoholic containers that was found inside the vehicle during the incident. I retrieved the Maryland driver license from Erick Portillo and the driver license was sent to the MVA along with other documents. Please see the attachment for the documents. Case closed All events occurred in Howard County, Maryland.
